{% doc %}
  Scroll Arrows
  Prev/Next chevron buttons for horizontal scroll sections (e.g.
  "you may also like" recommendations). Visible at all breakpoints so
  mobile users have the same affordance as desktop — earlier iteration
  was `hidden lg:flex` on the assumption that touch-swipe made arrows
  redundant on mobile, but Figma 68:72 (mobile PDP) explicitly shows
  them and they're useful for users who can't comfortably swipe (one-
  handed use, motor-accessibility). Buttons are 44×44 to meet the
  Apple HIG / WCAG 2.5.5 touch-target minimum.

  @example
    {% render 'scroll-arrows' %}
{% enddoc %}

<div class="flex items-center gap-3">
  <button type="button" class="w-11 h-11 inline-flex items-center justify-center text-muted" data-scroll-prev aria-label="Previous">
    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M10 12L6 8L10 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"/></svg>
  </button>
  <button type="button" class="w-11 h-11 inline-flex items-center justify-center text-fg" data-scroll-next aria-label="Next">
    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M6 4L10 8L6 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"/></svg>
  </button>
</div>